  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "The task to learn only with classes (A, B, C) and predict to categorize (A, B, C) or other unexpected D, F, or other classes is called open set recognition.",
    "In the open set recognition task, there are several categories (Fig. 1) assumed to characterize the learning models 10: (1) Known Known classes (KKCs): the samples are annotated by humans and given with the corresponding labels.",
    "(2) Known Unknown classes (KUCs) 11: The KUC is an umbrella term for different events, objects or concepts.",
    "It is hard to define the attribute of the KUC, which is usually a particular product incidental to the description of the subject of the thing.",
    "(3) Unknown Known classes 12: Classes for which no samples are available during training, but side information, such as semantic/ attribute information, is available."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
